# ── Security headers — SPEC, NOT LIVE ────────────────────────────────────────
# GitHub Pages (this site's origin) does not serve _headers — this file is inert
# HERE. It is kept as the source-of-truth spec and is mirrored by hand into the
# Cloudflare Response Header Transform Rules that run at the edge in front of
# andypeterson.dev. See docs/security-headers.md for the exact rules + rationale.
#
# The two headers that matter most for injection defense — the content security
# policy and the referrer policy — do NOT depend on the edge: they are also
# enforced in-page via <meta> (astro.config.mjs `security.csp` emits a hashed
# per-page policy at build time; BaseLayout.astro sets the referrer meta). The
# post-build gate scripts/check-security-headers.sh asserts the CSP actually
# ships in dist/. The headers below add edge-only defenses (nosniff, framing,
# HSTS, permissions) that a static origin cannot set for itself.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
/*
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  X-XSS-Protection: 0
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Permissions-Policy: camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=()
  Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=63072000; includeSubDomains; preload
